    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.161309>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Lebbeus longidactylus (Kobjakova, 1936), images showing colouration in life. A, ovigerous female (cl 23.5 mm), CBM-ZC 13526; B, male (cl 17.0 mm), same lot." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/161309/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.161310>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Lebbeus longidactylus (Kobjakova, 1936), ovigerous female (cl 23.5 mm), CBM-ZC 13526. A, anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages (left eye damaged), lateral view; B, rostrum and anterior part of carapace, lateral view; C, anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; D, orbital and anterolateral margins of carapace, right dorsolateral view; E, pleomeres 4 – 6, lateral view; F, telson, dorsal view; G, posterior part of telson, dorsal view; H, left antenna, ventral view (flagellum omitted); I, coxae of maxilliped 3 to pereopod 3, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/161310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.161311>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Lebbeus longidactylus (Kobjakova, 1936), ovigerous female (cl 23.5 mm), CBM-ZC 13526, left thoracic appendages. A, maxilliped 3, lateral view; B, same, distal part of ultimate article, dorsal view; C, same, distal part of antepenultimate article, lateral view; D, pereopod 1, lateral view; E, same, chela, extensor view; F, same, articulation between merus and ischium, showing details of armature, lateral view; G, pereopod 2, lateral view; H, pereopod 3, lateral view; I, same, dactylus, lateral view; J, same, distal part of dactylus, lateral view (pigmentation omitted); K, pereopod 4, lateral view; L, same, dactylus, lateral view; M, same, distal part of dactylus, lateral view (pigmentation omitted); N, pereopod 5, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/161311/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.161312>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Lebbeus longidactylus (Kobjakova, 1936), male (cl 17.0 mm), CBM-ZC 13526. A, anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, lateral view; B, endopod of left pleopod 1, ventral view; C, appendices interna and masculina of left pleopod 2, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/161312/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

